# Video frame images (JPG/PNG) extracted per clip. The clips are served via
# media_url (native <video>), so these per-frame images are not needed in the
# repo. They are regenerable from the source videos. Ignore repo-wide so they
# are never re-committed; use `git add -f` if you ever need to track one.
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png

# Large raw frame archive (~1.5GB) — not served; keep out of the repo.
*.tar

# Raw extracted frame source (~1GB of per-clip JPG/PNG + the source CSVs). The
# clips are encoded to mp4 under Videos/cholect50 and Videos/endoscapes; this
# nested source tree is the input to the generators, not served at runtime.
Videos/user_study_frames/
